The paper deals with the problem of machine learning with mislabeled training data, which is a common issue in various subfields of computer science such as machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), neural networks (cs.NE), and natural language processing (cs.CL). However, since the paper specifically focuses on the training of neural networks, cs.LG and cs.NE are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of multi-layered perceptrons (MLPs), which are commonly used in computer vision and image classification tasks, hence cs.CV is also a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the effects of noise on model performance, which is relevant to various sub-fields of computer science, including natural language processing (cs.CL).
